tmnxSonetGroupTable.name: tmnxSonetGroupTable
tmnxSonetGroupTable.description: The tmnxSonetGroupTable has an entry for each Tributary Unit Group(TUG3) on a path. On a port which supports unchannelized STS-3's, rows in this table are created when a channelized STS-3 has its tmnxSonetPathChildType set to sdhTug3. On a port which does not support unchannelized STS-3's, the rows in this table are implicitly created when a STS-3 is created in the tmnxSonetPathTable. Entries in this table are implicitly deleted when the parent entry of this group is deleted from the tmnxSonetPathTable or if the tmnxSonetPathChildType of the parent is set to something other than sdhTug3.

tmnxSonetGroupEntry.name: tmnxSonetGroupEntry
tmnxSonetGroupEntry.description: Each row entry represents a Tributary Unit Group(TUG3) on a path.

tmnxSonetGroupType.name: tmnxSonetGroupType
tmnxSonetGroupType.description: tmnxSonetGroupType indicates the sonet group type of this entry. For STS-3/STM-1 channelization, the value of this object will be 'sdhTug3'.

tmnxSonetGroupParentPortID.name: tmnxSonetGroupParentPortID
tmnxSonetGroupParentPortID.description: tmnxSonetGroupParentPortID indicates the TmnxPortID of the parent of this group.

tmnxSonetGroupChildType.name: tmnxSonetGroupChildType
tmnxSonetGroupChildType.description: tmnxSonetGroupChildType is used to configure the type of the children of this group. Based on the value of this object, entries of a certain channel type can be created in the tmnxSonetPathTable. For example, if the value of this object is set to 'sonetVt15', then 28 entries of type 'sonetVt15' can be created in the tmnxSonetPathTable.

tmnxSonetGroupName.name: tmnxSonetGroupName
tmnxSonetGroupName.description: tmnxSonetGroupName is the textual name for this sonet group.

tmnxCiscoHDLCTable.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCTable
tmnxCiscoHDLCTable.description: The tmnxCiscoHDLCTable has an entry for each port in the system that is configured for Cisco HDLC. It contains the parameters related to Cisco HDLC protocol on this port.

tmnxCiscoHDLCEntry.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCEntry
tmnxCiscoHDLCEntry.description: The tmnxCiscoHDLCEntry specifies parameters for a particular interfaces running Cisco HDLC encapsulation. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxCiscoHDLCKeepAliveInt.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCKeepAliveInt
tmnxCiscoHDLCKeepAliveInt.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCKeepAliveInt specifies the interval in seconds used for sending periodic keepalive packets. The default value is set to 10 seconds. A value of 0 specifies that the keepalive function is turned off. It is expected that the nodes at the two endpoints of the Cisco HDLC link are provisioned with the same values.

tmnxCiscoHDLCUpCount.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCUpCount
tmnxCiscoHDLCUpCount.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCUpCount specifies the number of continual keepalive packets that has to be received to declare the link up. It is expected that the nodes at the two endpoints of the Cisco HDLC link are provisioned with the same values.

tmnxCiscoHDLCDownCount.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCDownCount
tmnxCiscoHDLCDownCount.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCDownCount specifies the number of 'tmnxCiscoHDLCKeepAliveInt' intervals that must pass without receiving a keepalive packet before the link is declared down. It is expected that the nodes at the two endpoints of the Cisco HDLC link are provisioned with the same values.

tmnxCiscoHDLCOperState.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCOperState
tmnxCiscoHDLCOperState.description: The value of tmnxCiscoHDLCOperState indicates the operational status of the Cisco HDLC protocol for this port.

tmnxCiscoHDLCStatsTable.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatsTable
tmnxCiscoHDLCStatsTable.description: The tmnxCiscoHDLCStatsTable has an entry for each port in the system that is configured for Cisco HDLC encapsulation. It contains Cisco HDLC protocol statistics for the particular port.

tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatInPkts.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatInPkts
tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatInPkts.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatInPkts indicates the number of inbound Cisco HDLC packets discarded.

tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatOutPkts.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatOutPkts
tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatOutPkts.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCDiscardStatOutPkts indicates the number of outbound Cisco HDLC packets discarded.

tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInPkts.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInPkts
tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInPkts.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInPkts indicates the number of inbound Cisco HDLC packets.

tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutPkts.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutPkts
tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutPkts.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutPkts indicates the number of outbound Cisco HDLC packets.

tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInOctets.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInOctets
tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInOctets.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatInOctets indicates the number of inbound Cisco HDLC octets.

tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutOctets.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutOctets
tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutOctets.description: tmnxCiscoHDLCStatOutOctets indicates the number of outbound Cisco HDLC octets.

tmnxFRDlcmiTable.name: tmnxFRDlcmiTable
tmnxFRDlcmiTable.description: The tmnxFRDlcmiTable has an entry for each port in the system that is configured for Frame Relay. It contains the parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface (DLCMI) for the frame relay service on this port.

tmnxFRDlcmiEntry.name: tmnxFRDlcmiEntry
tmnxFRDlcmiEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular Data Link Connection Management Interface. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxFRDlcmiMode.name: tmnxFRDlcmiMode
tmnxFRDlcmiMode.description: tmnxFRDlcmiMode is used to set the mode of the interface. It can be set as Data terminal equipment (dte), Data circuit-terminating equipment (dce) or both as Data terminal equipment and Data circuit-terminating equipment (bidir).

tmnxFRDlcmiN392Dce.name: tmnxFRDlcmiN392Dce
tmnxFRDlcmiN392Dce.description: tmnxFRDlcmiN392Dce is used to configure the LMI error threshold for DCE interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiN393Dce.name: tmnxFRDlcmiN393Dce
tmnxFRDlcmiN393Dce.description: tmnxFRDlcmiN393Dce is used to configure the LMI monitored event count for DCE interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiT392Dce.name: tmnxFRDlcmiT392Dce
tmnxFRDlcmiT392Dce.description: tmnxFRDlcmiT392Dce is used to configure the polling verification timer for the Frame Relay DCE interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusEnqMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusEnqMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusEnqMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusEnqMsgs indicates the number of LMI Status Enquiry messages transmitted on this Frame Relay interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusEnqMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusEnqMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusEnqMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusEnqMsgs indicates the number of LMI Status Enquiry messages received on this Frame Relay interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiStatusEnqMsgTimeouts.name: tmnxFRDlcmiStatusEnqMsgTimeouts
tmnxFRDlcmiStatusEnqMsgTimeouts.description: tmnxFRDlcmiStatusEnqMsgTimeouts indicates the number of times the LMI agent did not receive a Status Enquiry message within the allotted time.

tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiTxStatusMsgs indicates the number of LMI Status messages transmitted on this Frame Relay interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiRxStatusMsgs indicates the number of LMI Status messages received on this Frame Relay interface.

tmnxFRDlcmiStatusMsgTimeouts.name: tmnxFRDlcmiStatusMsgTimeouts
tmnxFRDlcmiStatusMsgTimeouts.description: tmnxFRDlcmiStatusMsgTimeouts indicates the number of times the LMI agent did not receive a Status message within the allotted time.

tmnxFRDlcmiDiscardedMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiDiscardedMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiDiscardedMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiDiscardedMsgs indicates the number of times the LMI agent discarded a received message because it wasn't expecting it, the type of message was incorrect, or the contents of the message were invalid.

tmnxFRDlcmiInvRxSeqNumMsgs.name: tmnxFRDlcmiInvRxSeqNumMsgs
tmnxFRDlcmiInvRxSeqNumMsgs.description: tmnxFRDlcmiInvRxSeqNumMsgs indicates the number of times the LMI agent received a message with an invalid receive sequence number: i.e. a sequence number that does not match the last transmitted sequence number of the agent.

tmnxQosPoolAppTable.name: tmnxQosPoolAppTable
tmnxQosPoolAppTable.description: This table maintains associations of the buffer pools with the individual objects.

tmnxQosPoolAppEntry.name: tmnxQosPoolAppEntry
tmnxQosPoolAppEntry.description: This entry maintains the specifics about the association of a buffer pool and an object.

tmnxObjectType.name: tmnxObjectType
tmnxObjectType.description: The object tmnxObjectType defines the type of object to which the pool is being setup for.

tmnxObjectId.name: tmnxObjectId
tmnxObjectId.description: tmnxObjectId is used to identify the specific object. If tmnxObjectType is 'mda', then the tmnxObjectId is encoded as a physical port with the port being '0'. For all other types the encoding is done as per the description of TmnxPortID.

tmnxObjectAppType.name: tmnxObjectAppType
tmnxObjectAppType.description: The object tmnxObjectAppType specifies the nature of usage the pool would be used for. The pools could be used for access or network traffic at either ingress or egress.

tmnxObjectAppPool.name: tmnxObjectAppPool
tmnxObjectAppPool.description: tmnxObjectAppPool specifies the name of the pool to be used/created.

tmnxObjectAppPoolRowStatus.name: tmnxObjectAppPoolRowStatus
tmnxObjectAppPoolRowStatus.description: The object tmnxObjectAppPoolRowStatus is used to create or remove a pool application to the object.

tmnxObjectAppResvCbs.name: tmnxObjectAppResvCbs
tmnxObjectAppResvCbs.description: The percentage of pool size reserved for CBS. The value '-1' implies that the reserved CBS should be computed as the sum of the CBS requested by the entities using this pool if the application point is 'network'. For 'access' application points the value '-1' means a default of 30%.

tmnxObjectAppSlopePolicy.name: tmnxObjectAppSlopePolicy
tmnxObjectAppSlopePolicy.description: tmnxObjectAppSlopePolicy specifies the slope policy being used for this pool. The Slope policies define the nature of the RED Slopes for the high and the low priority traffic.

tmnxObjectAppPoolSize.name: tmnxObjectAppPoolSize
tmnxObjectAppPoolSize.description: Size in percentage of buffer space. The value '-1' implies that the pool size should be computed as per fair weighing between all other pools.

tmnxATMIntfTable.name: tmnxATMIntfTable
tmnxATMIntfTable.description: The tmnxATMIntfTable has an entry for each port/channel in the system that is configured for ATM. It contains ATM cell layer configuration parameters.

tmnxATMIntfEntry.name: tmnxATMIntfEntry
tmnxATMIntfEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular ATM Cell Management Interface. Entries cannot be created or deleted via SNMP SET operations. Entries will exist in this table when ATM encapsulation is configured on the port/channel.

tmnxATMIntfCellFormat.name: tmnxATMIntfCellFormat
tmnxATMIntfCellFormat.description: tmnxATMIntfCellFormat is used to set the cell format (UNI or NNI) that is to be used on the ATM interface.

tmnxATMIntfMinVpValue.name: tmnxATMIntfMinVpValue
tmnxATMIntfMinVpValue.description: tmnxATMIntfMinVpValue is used to set the minimum allowable VPI value that can be used on the ATM interface for a VPC.

tmnxATMIntfMapping.name: tmnxATMIntfMapping
tmnxATMIntfMapping.description: The value of tmnxATMIntfMapping specifies the cell mapping that is to be used on this ATM interface. When tmnxPortChanType does not have a value of 'pdhDs3 (14)', 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned to SNMP SET requests. When tmnxPortChanType has a value of 'pdhDs3 (14)', tmnxATMIntfMapping can be set to 'plcp (2)'.

tmnxPortNetIngressStatsTable.name: tmnxPortNetIngressStatsTable
tmnxPortNetIngressStatsTable.description: Defines the Alcatel 7x50 SR series network port ingress statistics table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of retrieving the traffic statistics for the physical queues being used for the ports to forward the network ingress traffic.

tmnxPortNetIngressStatsEntry.name: tmnxPortNetIngressStatsEntry
tmnxPortNetIngressStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in tmnxPortNetIngressStatsTable. Entries are created and deleted by the system depending on the queue policy being used at the specific port.

tmnxPortNetIngressQueueIndex.name: tmnxPortNetIngressQueueIndex
tmnxPortNetIngressQueueIndex.description: tmnxPortNetIngressQueueIndex serves as the tertiary index. When used in conjunction with tmnxChassisIndex and tmnxPortPortID, it uniquely identifies a network ingress queue for the specified port in the managed system.

tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network ingress packets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network ingress packets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfOcts
tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdInProfOcts indicates the number of conforming network ingress octets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfOcts
tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressFwdOutProfOcts indicates the number of exceeding network ingress octets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network ingress packets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network ingress packets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfOcts
tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressDroInProfOcts indicates the number of conforming network ingress octets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfOcts
tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetIngressDroOutProfOcts indicates the number of exceeding network ingress octets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressStatsTable.name: tmnxPortNetEgressStatsTable
tmnxPortNetEgressStatsTable.description: Defines the Alcatel 7x50 SR series network port egress statistics table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of retrieving the traffic statistics for the physical queues being used for the ports to forward the network egress traffic.

tmnxPortNetEgressStatsEntry.name: tmnxPortNetEgressStatsEntry
tmnxPortNetEgressStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in tmnxPortNetEgressStatsTable. Entries are created and deleted by the system depending on the queue policy being used at the specific port.

tmnxPortNetEgressQueueIndex.name: tmnxPortNetEgressQueueIndex
tmnxPortNetEgressQueueIndex.description: tmnxPortNetEgressQueueIndex serves as the tertiary index. When used in conjunction with tmnxChassisIndex and tmnxPortPortID, it uniquely identifies a network egress queue for the specified port in the managed system.

tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network egress packets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network egress packets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdInProfOcts indicates the number of conforming network egress octets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressFwdOutProfOcts indicates the number of exceeding network egress octets forwarded on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network egress packets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfPkts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network egress packets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressDroInProfOcts indicates the number of conforming network egress octets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfOcts.description: tmnxPortNetEgressDroOutProfOcts indicates the number of exceeding network egress octets dropped on this port using this queue.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsTable.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsTable
tmnxMcMlpppStatsTable.description: Defines the Alcatel 7x50 SR series Multiclass MLPPP statistics table for providing the capability of retrieving the traffic statistics for the physical queues being used for a class of a multiclass MLPPP bundle to forward the traffic.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsEntry.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsEntry
tmnxMcMlpppStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in tmnxMcMlpppStatsTable. Entries are created and deleted by the system depending on the number of classes being used by a given MLPPP bundle.

tmnxMcMlpppClassIndex.name: tmnxMcMlpppClassIndex
tmnxMcMlpppClassIndex.description: tmnxMcMlpppClassIndex serves as the tertiary index. When used in conjunction with tmnxChassisIndex and tmnxBundleBundleID, it uniquely identifies a class of a multiclass MLPPP bundle in the managed system.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressOct.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressOct
tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressOct.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressOct indicates the total number of octets in all packets received on the bundle for the given class on ingress before reassembly.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressPkt.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressPkt
tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressPkt.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressPkt indicates the total number of packets forwarded on the bundle for the given class on ingress towards higher layer protocols.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressErrPkt.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressErrPkt
tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressErrPkt.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsIngressErrPkt indicates the total number of packets discarded due to reassembly errors on the bundle for the given class on ingress.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressOct.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressOct
tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressOct.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressOct indicates the total number of octets in all packets received on the bundle for the given class on egress before segmentation.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressPkt.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressPkt
tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressPkt.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressPkt indicates the total number of packets forwarded on the bundle for the given class on egress towards the line.

tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressErrPkt.name: tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressErrPkt
tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressErrPkt.description: The value of tmnxMcMlpppStatsEgressErrPkt indicates the total number of packets discarded due to segmentation errors on the bundle for the given class on egress.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTable.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTable
tmnxBundleImaGrpTable.description: The tmnxBundleImaGrpTable contains IMA Group data

tmnxBundleImaGrpEntry.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpEntry
tmnxBundleImaGrpEntry.description: Each row entry contains data on an IMA Group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkActTimer.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkActTimer
tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkActTimer.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkActTimer specifies the Link Activation Timer used to clear an existing LIF, LODS and FRI-IMA alarm. The time specified determines how long is needed for member links to stabilize before being activated.

tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkDeactTimer.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkDeactTimer
tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkDeactTimer.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpLnkDeactTimer specifies the Link Deactivation Timer used to raise an LIF, LODS and FRI-IMA alarm. The time specified determines how long before a member link is declared in error and is deactivated.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSymmetryMode.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSymmetryMode
tmnxBundleImaGrpSymmetryMode.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSymmetryMode specifies the type of cell rate transfer over the virtual link.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTxId.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxId
tmnxBundleImaGrpTxId.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxId specifies the IMA Id generated at group creation time used by the near-end.

tmnxBundleImaGrpRxId.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxId
tmnxBundleImaGrpRxId.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxId specifies the IMA ID generated at group creation time used by the far-end.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTxRefLnk.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxRefLnk
tmnxBundleImaGrpTxRefLnk.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxRefLnk specifies the IMA bundle member that was selected to be the transmit timing reference link. If no member has been selected as the reference link a value of zero is returned.

tmnxBundleImaGrpRxRefLnk.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxRefLnk
tmnxBundleImaGrpRxRefLnk.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxRefLnk specifies the IMA bundle member that was detected to be the receive timing reference link. If no member has been detected as the reference link a value of zero is returned.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSmNeState.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmNeState
tmnxBundleImaGrpSmNeState.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmNeState specifies the current state of the IMA Group for the near-end.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFeState.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFeState
tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFeState.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFeState specifies the current state of the IMA Group for the far-end.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFailState.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFailState
tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFailState.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmFailState specifies the current state of the IMA Group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSmDownSecs.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmDownSecs
tmnxBundleImaGrpSmDownSecs.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmDownSecs specifies the number of seconds that the IMA Group State Machine is not Operational.

tmnxBundleImaGrpSmOperSecs.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmOperSecs
tmnxBundleImaGrpSmOperSecs.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpSmOperSecs specifies the number of seconds that the IMA Group State Machine has been in the Operational State.

tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailTxCR.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailTxCR
tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailTxCR.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailTxCR specifies the available transmit bandwidth on this IMA group. It only considers members that are in the Active State.

tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailRxCR.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailRxCR
tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailRxCR.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpAvailRxCR specifies the available bandwidth on this IMA group in the receive direction. It only considers members that are in the Active State.

tmnxBundleImaGrpNeFails.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpNeFails
tmnxBundleImaGrpNeFails.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpNeFails specifies the number of reported IMA Group failures since boot time.

tmnxBundleImaGrpFeFails.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpFeFails
tmnxBundleImaGrpFeFails.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpFeFails specifies the number of reported IMA Group far-end failures since boot time.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxIcpCells
tmnxBundleImaGrpTxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxIcpCells specifies number of transmitted ICP cells for this IMA Group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpRxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxIcpCells
tmnxBundleImaGrpRxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpRxIcpCells specifies number of received ICP cells for this IMA Group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpErrorIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpErrorIcpCells
tmnxBundleImaGrpErrorIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpErrorIcpCells specifies number of ICP cells with HEC or CRC-10 errors.

tmnxBundleImaGrpLostRxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpLostRxIcpCells
tmnxBundleImaGrpLostRxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpLostRxIcpCells specifies the number of missing ICP cells at the expected offset.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTxOamLablVal.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxOamLablVal
tmnxBundleImaGrpTxOamLablVal.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTxOamLablVal specifies near-end value to be transmitted.

tmnxBundleImaGrpAlphaValue.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpAlphaValue
tmnxBundleImaGrpAlphaValue.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpAlphaValue specifies the number of consecutive ICP cells that need to be detected before moving from the IMA Sync State to the IMA Hunt State.

tmnxBundleImaGrpBetaValue.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpBetaValue
tmnxBundleImaGrpBetaValue.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpBetaValue specifies the number of consecutive errored ICP cells that need to be detected before moving from the IMA Sync State to the IMA Hunt State

tmnxBundleImaGrpGammaValue.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpGammaValue
tmnxBundleImaGrpGammaValue.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpGammaValue specifies the number of consecutive valid ICP cells that need to be detected before moving from the IMA pre-Sync State to the IMA Hunt State.

tmnxBundleImaGrpNeClockMode.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpNeClockMode
tmnxBundleImaGrpNeClockMode.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpNeClockMode specifies near-end transmit clock mode.

tmnxBundleImaGrpFeClockMode.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpFeClockMode
tmnxBundleImaGrpFeClockMode.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpFeClockMode specifies far-end transmit clock mode.

tmnxBundleImaGrpVersion.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpVersion
tmnxBundleImaGrpVersion.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpVersion specifies the IMA Version for this group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpMaxConfBw.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpMaxConfBw
tmnxBundleImaGrpMaxConfBw.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpMaxConfBw specifies the number of links that is used to determine the maximum configurable bandwidth that is allowed to be used for this IMA group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState
tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState specifies the current state of the test pattern procedure. A value of 'disabled' specifies that the group is currently not running. A value of 'operating' enables the test pattern procedure. The test pattern procedure continues until it is 'disabled'.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTestMember.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestMember
tmnxBundleImaGrpTestMember.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestMember specifies a member link to be used for the test pattern procedure. A value of zero indicates that no member link has been selected. When tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState does not have the value 'disabled', an attempt to set this object will be rejected with an inconsistentValue error.

tmnxBundleImaGrpTestPattern.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestPattern
tmnxBundleImaGrpTestPattern.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpTestPattern specifies the Transmit Test Pattern in an IMA group loopback operation. This value may only be changed when tmnxBundleImaGrpTestState is 'disabled'.

tmnxBundleImaGrpDiffDelayMaxObs.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpDiffDelayMaxObs
tmnxBundleImaGrpDiffDelayMaxObs.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpDiffDelayMaxObs indicates the latest maximum differential delay observed between links having the least and most link propagation delay among the received links configured in this IMA group.

tmnxBundleImaGrpLeastDelayLink.name: tmnxBundleImaGrpLeastDelayLink
tmnxBundleImaGrpLeastDelayLink.description: tmnxBundleImaGrpLeastDelayLink indicates a member link which has the smallest link propagation delay. If this delay has yet to be determined or no member link has been configured, a value of zero is returned.

tmnxBundleMemberImaTable.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaTable
tmnxBundleMemberImaTable.description: The tmnxBundleMemberImaTable has an entry for an IMA link associated with an IMA Group.

tmnxBundleMemberImaEntry.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaEntry
tmnxBundleMemberImaEntry.description: Each row entry represents an IMA link associated with an IMA Group.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxState
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxState indicates the state of near-end transmit IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxState
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxState indicates the state of near-end receive IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxState
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxState indicates the state of far-end transmit IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxState
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxState indicates the state of far-end receive IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxFailState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxFailState
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxFailState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxFailState indicates the IMA link failure reason for the near-end.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxFailState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxFailState
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxFailState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxFailState indicates the IMA link failure reason for the far-end.

tmnxBundleMemberImaTxLid.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaTxLid
tmnxBundleMemberImaTxLid.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaTxLid indicates the Link Identifier assigned to the transmit IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaRxLid.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxLid
tmnxBundleMemberImaRxLid.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxLid indicates the Link Identifier used on the receive IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaViolations.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaViolations
tmnxBundleMemberImaViolations.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaViolations indicates the number of ICP violations including errored, invalid or missing ICP cells.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeSevErrSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeSevErrSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeSevErrSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeSevErrSecs indicates the number of one second intervals in which thirty percent or more of the near-end ICP cells are in violation, or link defects have occurred.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeSevErrSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeSevErrSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeSevErrSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeSevErrSecs indicates the number of one second intervals in which the far-end contains IMA-RDI defects.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeUnavailSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeUnavailSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeUnavailSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeUnavailSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the near-end.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeUnavailSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeUnavailSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeUnavailSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeUnavailSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the near-end.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxUnuseSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxUnuseSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxUnuseSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxUnuseSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the near-end transmit link state machine.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxUnuseSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxUnuseSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxUnuseSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxUnuseSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the near-end receive link state machine.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxUnuseSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxUnuseSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxUnuseSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxUnuseSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the far-end transmit link state machine.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxUnuseSecs.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxUnuseSecs
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxUnuseSecs.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxUnuseSecs indicates the number of unavailable seconds at the far-end receive link state machine.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxNumFails.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxNumFails
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxNumFails.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeTxNumFails indicates the number of times that a near-end transmit alarm is set on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxNumFails.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxNumFails
tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxNumFails.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaNeRxNumFails indicates the number of times that a near-end receive alarm is set on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxNumFails.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxNumFails
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxNumFails.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeTxNumFails indicates the number of times that a far-end transmit alarm is set on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxNumFails.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxNumFails
tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxNumFails.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaFeRxNumFails indicates the number of times that a far-end receive alarm is set on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaTxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaTxIcpCells
tmnxBundleMemberImaTxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaTxIcpCells indicates the number of ICP cells that have been transmitted on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaRxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxIcpCells
tmnxBundleMemberImaRxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxIcpCells indicates the number of ICP cells that have been received on the IMA link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaErrorIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaErrorIcpCells
tmnxBundleMemberImaErrorIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaErrorIcpCells indicates the number of ICP cells with HEC or CRC-10 errors.

tmnxBundleMemberImaLstRxIcpCells.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaLstRxIcpCells
tmnxBundleMemberImaLstRxIcpCells.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaLstRxIcpCells indicates the number of lost ICP cells at the expected offset.

tmnxBundleMemberImaOifAnomalies.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaOifAnomalies
tmnxBundleMemberImaOifAnomalies.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaOifAnomalies indicates the number of OIF anomalies at the near-end.

tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestState.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestState
tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestState.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestState indicates the current state of the test pattern on this link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestPattern.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestPattern
tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestPattern.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaRxTestPattern indicates the received test pattern value on this link.

tmnxBundleMemberImaRelDelay.name: tmnxBundleMemberImaRelDelay
tmnxBundleMemberImaRelDelay.description: tmnxBundleMemberImaRelDelay indicates the latest measured delay on this member link relative to the member link with the least delay within the same IMA group

tmnxL4LoadBalancing.name: tmnxL4LoadBalancing
tmnxL4LoadBalancing.description: The value of tmnxL4LoadBalancing specifies whether layer 4 information, src and dst ports, should be used in the LAG and ECMP hashing algorithm. This is the global system setting that all ports will inherit. When set to 'true', src and dst ports are used in the hashing algorithm. The per port setting of tmnxPortLoadBalanceAlgorithm can override tmnxL4LoadBalancing.

tmnxDS1PortTable.name: tmnxDS1PortTable
tmnxDS1PortTable.description: The tmnxDS1PortTable has an entry for a DS1 physical port.

tmnxDS1PortEntry.name: tmnxDS1PortEntry
tmnxDS1PortEntry.description: Each row entry represents a physical DS1 port on a IOM card in a chassis in the system. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations. Entries in this table will be created automatically when the tmnxMDAAssignedType object is set to the DS1 MDA type The tmnxDS1PortEntry contains attributes that are unique to the 'ds1e1' TmnxPortType. The tmnxPortPortID contains the slot, mda and port numbers encoded into it. For each tmnxDS1PortEntry, there will be a corresponding entry in the tmnxPortTable and the ifTable.

tmnxDS1PortBuildout.name: tmnxDS1PortBuildout
tmnxDS1PortBuildout.description: tmnxDS1PortBuildout configures the cable buildout length. A ds1 port has two settings for the DS1 cable buildout: a 'short' setting, for cable lengths of less than or equal to 655 feet, and a 'long' setting for cable lengths of greater than 655 feet. This object applies to copper-cable-based DS1 ports only.

tmnxDS1PortLastChangeTime.name: tmnxDS1PortLastChangeTime
tmnxDS1PortLastChangeTime.description: The tmnxDS1PortLastChangeTime variable contains the sysUpTime value of the most recently modified writable variable in the tmnxDS1PortEntry row for this port.

tmnxDS1PortType.name: tmnxDS1PortType
tmnxDS1PortType.description: tmnxDS1PortType configures the type of the physical port to 'ds1', 'e1' or 'j1'.

tmnxDS1PortLineLength.name: tmnxDS1PortLineLength
tmnxDS1PortLineLength.description: tmnxDS1PortLineLength configuration only applies to a ds1 port configured with a 'short' buildout. tmnxDS1PortLineLength configures the length of the line (in feet). For line lengths longer than 655 feet configure the ds1 port buildout as 'long'. For 'long' buildout the following values are valid: lengthNotApplicable - Not applicable For 'short' buildout the following values are valid: length0To133 - For line length from 0 to 133 feet length134To266 - For line length from 134 to 266 feet length267To399 - For line length from 267 to 399 feet length400To533 - For line length from 400 to 533 feet length534To655 - For line length from 534 to 655 feet The default for 'long' buildout is 'lengthNotApplicable' while the default for 'short' buildout is 'length0To133'.

tmnxDS1PortLbo.name: tmnxDS1PortLbo
tmnxDS1PortLbo.description: tmnxDS1PortLbo configuration only applies to a ds1 port configured with a 'long' buildout. tmnxDS1PortLbo configures the number of decibels(dB) the transmission signal decreases over the line. For 'short' buildout the following values are valid: lboNotApplicable - Not applicable For 'long' buildout the following values are valid: lbo0dB - For 0 dB lboNeg7p5dB - For -7.5 dB lboNeg15p0dB - For -15.0 dB lboNeg22p5dB - For -22.5 dB The default for 'short' build out is 'lboNotApplicable' while the default for 'long' buildout is 'lbo0dB'

tmnxDS1PortDbGain.name: tmnxDS1PortDbGain
tmnxDS1PortDbGain.description: tmnxDS1PortDbGain only applies to a ds1 port configured with a 'long' buildout. tmnxDS1PortDbGain shows the number of decibels the received signal is increased to compensate for loss.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideTable.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideTable
tmnxPortSchedOverrideTable.description: The tmnxPortSchedOverrideTable has an entry for each port scheduler override configured on this system.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideEntry.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideEntry
tmnxPortSchedOverrideEntry.description: Each row represents a particular port-scheduler override. Entries are created and deleted by the user.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideRowStatus.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideRowStatus
tmnxPortSchedOverrideRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of port-scheduler overrides. When tmnxPortEgrPortSchedPlcy of the tmnxPortEntry indexed by the same indices of this table is an empty string, creation will fail.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideSchedName.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideSchedName
tmnxPortSchedOverrideSchedName.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideSchedName indicates the name of the port scheduler policy that this row entry overrides.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLastChanged.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLastChanged
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management change to this row.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideMaxRate.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideMaxRate
tmnxPortSchedOverrideMaxRate.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideMaxRate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyMaxRate.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 1. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl1PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl1CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 1. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl1CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 2. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl2PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl2CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 2. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl2CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 3. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl3PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl3CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 3. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl3CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 4. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl4PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl4CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 4. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl4CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 5. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl5PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl5CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 5. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl5CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 6. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl6PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl6CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 6. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl6CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 7. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl7PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl7CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 7. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl7CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8PIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8PIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8PIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8PIR specifies the total bandwidth limit, PIR, for priority level 8. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl8PIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8CIR.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8CIR
tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8CIR.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideLvl8CIR specifies the within-cir bandwidth limit for priority level 8. This object overrides ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tPortSchedulerPlcyLvl8CIR.

tmnxPortSchedOverrideFlags.name: tmnxPortSchedOverrideFlags
tmnxPortSchedOverrideFlags.description: The value of tmnxPortSchedOverrideFlags specifies the set of attributes whose values have been overridden via management on this port scheduler. Clearing a given flag will return the corresponding overridden attribute to the value defined in the port's port-scheduler policy.

tmnxBPGrpAssocTable.name: tmnxBPGrpAssocTable
tmnxBPGrpAssocTable.description: The tmnxBPGrpAssocTable has an entry for each Bundle Protection Group created on the system.

tmnxBPGrpAssocEntry.name: tmnxBPGrpAssocEntry
tmnxBPGrpAssocEntry.description: Each row displays the relationship between a Bundle Protection group and its working and protection bundle.

tmnxBPGrpAssocWorkingBundleID.name: tmnxBPGrpAssocWorkingBundleID
tmnxBPGrpAssocWorkingBundleID.description: tmnxBPGrpAssocWorkingBundleID identifies the working bundle. A value of zero is given if no working bundle is associated with the given tmnxBundleBundleID.

tmnxBPGrpAssocProtectBundleID.name: tmnxBPGrpAssocProtectBundleID
tmnxBPGrpAssocProtectBundleID.description: tmnxBPGrpAssocProtectBundleID identifies the protection bundle. A value of zero is given if no protection bundle is associated with the given tmnxBundleBundleID.

tmnxBPGrpAssocActiveBundleID.name: tmnxBPGrpAssocActiveBundleID
tmnxBPGrpAssocActiveBundleID.description: tmnxBPGrpAssocActiveBundleID identifies the bundle that is considered the active bundle. This bundle contains the members that are part of the active aps port. A value of zero is given if no bundle is considered active.

tmnxBundleMlpppTable.name: tmnxBundleMlpppTable
tmnxBundleMlpppTable.description: The tmnxBundleMlpppTable contains MLPPP specific data.

tmnxBundleMlpppEntry.name: tmnxBundleMlpppEntry
tmnxBundleMlpppEntry.description: Each row entry contains data on an MLPPP Bundle.

tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointID.name: tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointID
tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointID.description: tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointID indentifies the Endpoint Discriminator identifier value within the specified tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointIDClass. The object tmnxPortAdminStatus must be set to 'outOfService' to change this value.

tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointIDClass.name: tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointIDClass
tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointIDClass.description: tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointIDClass specifies the Link Control Protocol Endpoint Descriminator Class field type of the tmnxBundleMlpppEndpointID. The object tmnxPortAdminStatus must be set to 'outOfService' to change this value. Bundle DEFVAL Physical MLPPP Bundle ieee802dot1GlobalMacAddress (3) MLPPP Bundle Protection Group ipAddress (2)

tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount.name: tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount
tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount specifies whether Multiclass MLPPP is enabled on a bundle with a tmnxBundleType of 'mlppp' and when enabled what is the number of classes to be negotiated/supported over the MLPPP bundle. The value of 0 disables multiclass MLPPP including negotiation in the PPP protocol. All other values specify the number of classes to be supported on a given multiclass bundle and enable Multiclass MLPPP negotiation on that bundle. Non-zero values supported are platform/MDA specific. The value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount must be set to 0 and cannot be changed when LFI is enabled on the bundle (see tmnxBundleLFI object in tmnxBundleTable). The value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount may be modified only when tmnxBundleNumLinks is zero. To set the value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount to a value greater than 4, the long sequence format must be enabled on the bundle (see tmnxBundleShortSequence object in tmnxBundleTable). Changing the value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount resets the values of tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId and tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId to their defaults

tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId.name: tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId
tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId.description: tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId specifies ingress QoS profile to be used for the incoming traffic over this MLPPP bundle. The value of tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId may be modified only when the value of tmnxBundleNumLinks is 0. The value of tmnxBundleMlpppIngQoSProfId of 0 indicates a default QoS profile is used as applicable to a given H/W and the configured value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount.

tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId.name: tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId
tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId.description: tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId specifies egress QoS profile to be used for the outgoing traffic over this MLPPP bundle. The value of tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId may be modified only when tmnxBundleNumLinks is zero. The value of tmnxBundleMlpppEgrQoSProfId of 0 indicates a default profile is used as applicable to a given H/W and the configured value of tmnxBundleMlpppClassCount.

tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorTable.name: tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorTable
tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorTable.description: The tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorTable has an entry for each SFP/XFP in the system that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring (DDM). The table is indexed by TmnxPortID. Each row in this table is dynamically added and removed internally by the system based on the presence or absence of DDM capable SFP/XFP components.

tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorEntry.name: tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorEntry
tmnxDigitalDiagMonitorEntry.description: Each row represents a particular SFP/XFP that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring. Entries are created and deleted internally by the system.

tmnxDDMTemperature.name: tmnxDDMTemperature
tmnxDDMTemperature.description: The value of tmnxDDMTemperature indicates the current temperature of the SFP/XFP in degrees Celsius.

tmnxDDMTempLowWarning.name: tmnxDDMTempLowWarning
tmnxDDMTempLowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTempLowWarning indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in degrees Celsius that triggers a low-warning.

tmnxDDMTempLowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTempLowAlarm
tmnxDDMTempLowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTempLowAlarm indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in degrees Celsius that triggers a low-alarm.

tmnxDDMTempHiWarning.name: tmnxDDMTempHiWarning
tmnxDDMTempHiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTempHiWarning indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in degrees Celsius that triggers a hi-warning.

tmnxDDMTempHiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTempHiAlarm
tmnxDDMTempHiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTempHiAlarm indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in degrees Celsius that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMSupplyVoltage.name: tmnxDDMSupplyVoltage
tmnxDDMSupplyVoltage.description: The value of tmnxDDMSupplyVoltage indicates the current supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in micro-Volts (uV).

tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowWarning.name: tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowWarning
tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowWarning indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in micro-Volts (uV) that triggers a low-warning.

tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowAlarm
tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageLowAlarm indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in micro-Volts (uV) that triggers a low-alarm.

tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiWarning.name: tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiWarning
tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiWarning indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in micro-Volts (uV) that triggers a hi-warning.

tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiAlarm
tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMSupplyVoltageHiAlarm indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in micro-Volts (uV) that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrent.name: tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrent
tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrent.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrent indicates the current Transmit Bias Current of the SFP/XFP in micro-Amperes (uA).

tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowWarning.name: tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowWarning
tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowWarning indicates the Transmit Bias Current of the SFP/XFP in micro-Amperes (uA) that triggers a low-warning.

tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowAlarm
tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentLowAlarm indicates the Transmit Bias Current of the SFP/XFP in micro-Amperes (uA) that triggers a low-alarm.

tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiWarning.name: tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiWarning
tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiWarning indicates the Transmit Bias Current of the SFP/XFP in micro-Amperes (uA) that triggers a hi-warning.

tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiAlarm
tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxBiasCurrentHiAlarm indicates the Transmit Bias Current of the SFP/XFP in micro-Amperes (uA) that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMTxOutputPower.name: tmnxDDMTxOutputPower
tmnxDDMTxOutputPower.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxOutputPower indicates the current Output Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW).

tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowWarning.name: tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowWarning
tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowWarning indicates the Output Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a low-warning.

tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowAlarm
tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerLowAlarm indicates the Output Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a low-alarm.

tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiWarning.name: tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiWarning
tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiWarning indicates the Output Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiAlarm
tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMTxOutputPowerHiAlarm indicates the Output Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPower.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPower
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPower.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPower indicates the current Received Optical Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW).

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowWarning.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowWarning
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowWarning indicates the Received Optical Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a low-warning.

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowAlarm
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerLowAlarm indicates the Received Optical Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a low-alarm.

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiWarning.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiWarning
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiWarning indicates the Received Optical Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a hi-warning.

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiAlarm
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerHiAlarm indicates the Received Optical Power of the SFP/XFP in micro-Watts (uW) that triggers a hi-alarm.

tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerType.name: tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerType
tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerType.description: The value of tmnxDDMRxOpticalPowerType indicates whether the tmnxDDMRxOpticalPower was taken as an average, or as an Optical Modulation Amplitude (OMA).

tmnxDDMAux1.name: tmnxDDMAux1
tmnxDDMAux1.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1 indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 information of the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux1LowWarning.name: tmnxDDMAux1LowWarning
tmnxDDMAux1LowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1LowWarning indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 low-warning threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux1LowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMAux1LowAlarm
tmnxDDMAux1LowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1LowAlarm indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 low-alarm threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux1HiWarning.name: tmnxDDMAux1HiWarning
tmnxDDMAux1HiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1HiWarning indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 hi-warning threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux1HiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMAux1HiAlarm
tmnxDDMAux1HiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1HiAlarm indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 hi-alarm threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux1Type.name: tmnxDDMAux1Type
tmnxDDMAux1Type.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux1Type indicates the measurement type of the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 1 information of the XFP: none (0) - not specified. adp-bias-voltage (1) - LSB is 10mV. reserved-2 (2) - reserved for future use. tec-current (3) - LSB is 100uA. laser-temp (4) - degrees Celsius(C). laser-wavelength (5) - LSB is 0.05 nm. voltage-50 (6) - 5.0 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-33 (7) - 3.3 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-18 (8) - 1.8 supply voltage, LSB=100uV, voltage-52 (9) - -5.2 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. current-50 (10) - 5.0V supply current, LSB=100uA. reserved-11 (11) - reserved for future use. reserved-12 (12) - reserved for future use. current-33 (13) - 3.3V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-18 (14) - 1.8V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-52 (15) - -5.2V supply current, LSB=100uA.

tmnxDDMAux2.name: tmnxDDMAux2
tmnxDDMAux2.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2 indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 information of the SFP/XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2LowWarning.name: tmnxDDMAux2LowWarning
tmnxDDMAux2LowWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2LowWarning indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 low-warning threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2LowAlarm.name: tmnxDDMAux2LowAlarm
tmnxDDMAux2LowAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2LowAlarm indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 low-alarm threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2HiWarning.name: tmnxDDMAux2HiWarning
tmnxDDMAux2HiWarning.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2HiWarning indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 hi-warning threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm
tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 hi-alarm threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2Type.name: tmnxDDMAux2Type
tmnxDDMAux2Type.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2Type indicates the measurement type of the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 information of the XFP: none (0) - not specified. adp-bias-voltage (1) - LSB is 10mV. reserved-2 (2) - reserved for future use. tec-current (3) - LSB is 100uA. laser-temp (4) - degrees Celsius(C). laser-wavelength (5) - LSB is 0.05 nm. voltage-50 (6) - 5.0 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-33 (7) - 3.3 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-18 (8) - 1.8 supply voltage, LSB=100uV, voltage-52 (9) - -5.2 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. current-50 (10) - 5.0V supply current, LSB=100uA. reserved-11 (11) - reserved for future use. reserved-12 (12) - reserved for future use. current-33 (13) - 3.3V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-18 (14) - 1.8V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-52 (15) - -5.2V supply current, LSB=100uA.

tmnxDDMFailedThresholds.name: tmnxDDMFailedThresholds
tmnxDDMFailedThresholds.description: The value of tmnxDDMFailedThresholds indicates which objects of the monitored SFP/XFP is in a failed or cleared threshold state. A set bit indicates that the specified threshold has been exceeded.

tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated.name: tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated
tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated.description: The value of tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated indicates whether the SFP was externally calibrated (true) or internally calibrated (false).

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4 indicates the Rx_PWR(4) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3 indicates the Rx_PWR(3) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8462 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2 indicates the Rx_PWR(2) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1 indicates the Rx_PWR(1) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0 indicates the Rx_PWR(0) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope indicates the Tx_l(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset indicates the Tx_l(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope indicates the Tx_PWR(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset indicates the Tx_PWR(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope indicates the T(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset indicates the T(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope indicates the V(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset indicates the V(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxPortNotifyPortId.name: tmnxPortNotifyPortId
tmnxPortNotifyPortId.description: Used by tmnx port Notifications, the OID indicates the port or sonet path associated with the alarm.

tmnxPortNotifySonetAlarmReason.name: tmnxPortNotifySonetAlarmReason
tmnxPortNotifySonetAlarmReason.description: Used by tmnx sonet Port Notifications, the value of tmnxPortNotifySonetAlarmReason indicates the reason a sonet port alarm has been raised.

tmnxPortNotifySonetPathAlarmReason.name: tmnxPortNotifySonetPathAlarmReason
tmnxPortNotifySonetPathAlarmReason.description: Used by tmnx sonet path Notifications, the value of tmnxPortNotifySonetPathAlarmReason indicates the reason a sonet path alarm has been raised.

tmnxPortNotifyError.name: tmnxPortNotifyError
tmnxPortNotifyError.description: Used by tmnxEqPortError notification, the value of tmnxPortNotifyError indicates the reason a port has an error.

tmnxPortNotifyDS3AlarmReason.name: tmnxPortNotifyDS3AlarmReason
tmnxPortNotifyDS3AlarmReason.description: Used by tmnx DS3 Port Notifications, the value of tmnxPortNotifyDS3AlarmReason indicates the reason a DS3 interface alarm has been raised.

tmnxPortNotifyDS1AlarmReason.name: tmnxPortNotifyDS1AlarmReason
tmnxPortNotifyDS1AlarmReason.description: Used by tmnx DS1 Port Notifications, the value of tmnxPortNotifyDS1AlarmReason indicates the reason a DS1 interface alarm has been raised.

tmnxPortNotifyBundleId.name: tmnxPortNotifyBundleId
tmnxPortNotifyBundleId.description: Used by tmnx bundle Notifications, the value indicates the bundle associated with the alarm.

tmnxPortNotifyEtherAlarmReason.name: tmnxPortNotifyEtherAlarmReason
tmnxPortNotifyEtherAlarmReason.description: Used by tmnx ethernet Port Notifications, the value of tmnxPortNotifyEtherAlarmReason indicates the reason a ethernet port alarm has been raised.

tmnxDDMFailedObject.name: tmnxDDMFailedObject
tmnxDDMFailedObject.description: Used by Digital Diagnostic Monitoring (DDM) Notifications, the value of tmnxDDMFailedObject indicates which object of the monitored SFP/XFP is in a failed or cleared threshold state.

tmnxEqOobPortFailure.name: tmnxEqOobPortFailure
tmnxEqOobPortFailure.description: Generated when the out-of-band Ethernet port has failed. On the Alcatel 7x50 SR system, the out-of-band port is the CPM management interface. This notification was made obsolete in the 2.1 release. The Out-of-band, OOB, port is what id refered to as the management port or cpm port. It has an entry in ifTable and linkup, linkDown and tmnxEqPortError notifications are sent for the management port just as for any other port in the system.

tmnxEqPortFailure.name: tmnxEqPortFailure
tmnxEqPortFailure.description: Generated when a port has failed. This notification was made obsolete in the 2.1 release. tmnxEqPortError is used instead of tmnxEqPortFailure. Standard IETF linkDown notification is sent when a physical port failure is detected. tmnxEqPortError is sent with a ASCII reason message when port errors are detected. It was originally intended that tmnxEqPortError be used to report errors that do not cause port state change to 'down'. tmnxEqPortFailure was intended to report errors that do cause the port state change to 'down'. However, in the implementation tmnxEqPortError is used for both fatal and non-fatal errors.

tmnxEqPortSonetAlarm.name: tmnxEqPortSonetAlarm
tmnxEqPortSonetAlarm.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH port alarm condition is detected. It is generated only when the type of alarm being raised is enabled in tmnxSonetReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortSonetAlarmClear.name: tmnxEqPortSonetAlarmClear
tmnxEqPortSonetAlarmClear.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH port alarm condition is cleared. It is generated only when the type of alarm being cleared is enabled in tmnxSonetReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarm.name: tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarm
tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarm.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH path alarm condition is detected. It is generated only when the type of alarm being raised is enabled in tmnxSonetPathReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarmClear.name: tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarmClear
tmnxEqPortSonetPathAlarmClear.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH path alarm condition is cleared. It is generated only when the type of alarm being cleared is enabled in tmnxSonetPathReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortSFPInserted.name: tmnxEqPortSFPInserted
tmnxEqPortSFPInserted.description: Generated when a SFP is inserted in the port.

tmnxEqPortSFPRemoved.name: tmnxEqPortSFPRemoved
tmnxEqPortSFPRemoved.description: Generated when a SFP is removed from the port.

tmnxEqPortWrongSFP.name: tmnxEqPortWrongSFP
tmnxEqPortWrongSFP.description: Generated when a wrong type of SFP optics module is plugged into a 1 Gig MDA, SONET MDA, or 100FX MDA. Because of the large variety of SFPs now supported and their different encoding schemes for compliance bits, the check for wrong SFP has been removed. As a result, tmnxEqPortWrongSFP notification is no longer generated. However, wrong SFP can be inferred from port statistics.

tmnxEqPortSFPCorrupted.name: tmnxEqPortSFPCorrupted
tmnxEqPortSFPCorrupted.description: Generated when SFP information stored in the EPROM on the SFP is corrupt. This notification was made obsolete for revision 6.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems; it was replaced by tmnxEqPortSFPStatusFailure.

tmnxPortNotifyBerSdTca.name: tmnxPortNotifyBerSdTca
tmnxPortNotifyBerSdTca.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH port's signal degradation bit error rate is greater than the configured error rate threshold. This notification was made obsolete in the 2.1 release.

tmnxPortNotifyBerSfTca.name: tmnxPortNotifyBerSfTca
tmnxPortNotifyBerSfTca.description: Generated when a SONET/SDH port's signal failure bit error rate is greater than the configured error rate threshold. This notification was made obsolete in the 2.1 release.

tmnxEqPortError.name: tmnxEqPortError
tmnxEqPortError.description: Generated when an error listed in tmnxPortNotifyError is detected on the port.

tmnxEqPortDS3Alarm.name: tmnxEqPortDS3Alarm
tmnxEqPortDS3Alarm.description: Generated when a DS3 interface alarm condition is detected. It is generated only when the type of alarm being raised is enabled in tmnxDS3ChannelReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortDS3AlarmClear.name: tmnxEqPortDS3AlarmClear
tmnxEqPortDS3AlarmClear.description: Generated when a DS3 interface alarm condition is cleared. It is generated only when the type of alarm being cleared is enabled in tmnxDS3ChannelReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortDS1Alarm.name: tmnxEqPortDS1Alarm
tmnxEqPortDS1Alarm.description: Generated when a DS1 interface alarm condition is detected. It is generated only when the type of alarm being raised is enabled in tmnxDS1ReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortDS1AlarmClear.name: tmnxEqPortDS1AlarmClear
tmnxEqPortDS1AlarmClear.description: Generated when a DS1 interface alarm condition is cleared. It is generated only when the type of alarm being cleared is enabled in tmnxDS1ReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortBndlYellowDiffExceeded.name: tmnxEqPortBndlYellowDiffExceeded
tmnxEqPortBndlYellowDiffExceeded.description: Generated when the differential delay of a port in the bundle exceeds the configured value in tmnxBundleYellowDiffDelay.

tmnxEqPortBndlRedDiffExceeded.name: tmnxEqPortBndlRedDiffExceeded
tmnxEqPortBndlRedDiffExceeded.description: Generated when the differential delay of a port in the bundle exceeds the configured value in tmnxBundleRedDiffDelay.

tmnxEqPortBndlBadEndPtDiscr.name: tmnxEqPortBndlBadEndPtDiscr
tmnxEqPortBndlBadEndPtDiscr.description: Generated when the port detected mismatched peer endpoint discriminator for the bundle.

tmnxEqPortEtherAlarm.name: tmnxEqPortEtherAlarm
tmnxEqPortEtherAlarm.description: tmnxEqPortEtherAlarm is generated when a ethernet port alarm condition is detected. It is generated only when the type of alarm being raised is enabled in tmnxPortEtherReportAlarm.

tmnxEqPortEtherAlarmClear.name: tmnxEqPortEtherAlarmClear
tmnxEqPortEtherAlarmClear.description: tmnxEqPortEtherAlarmClear is generated when a ethernet port alarm condition is cleared. It is generated only when the type of alarm being cleared is enabled in tmnxPortEtherReportAlarm.

tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStarted.name: tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStarted
tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStarted.description: The tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStarted notification is generated when a loopback is provisioned on a DS1/E1 port.

tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStopped.name: tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStopped
tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStopped.description: The tmnxDS1E1LoopbackStopped notification is generated when a loopback is removed on a DS1/E1 port. The value of tmnxSonetLoopback specifies the type of loopback that was configured and has now been removed.

tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStarted.name: tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStarted
tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStarted.description: The tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStarted notification is generated when a loopback is provisioned on a DS3/E3 port.

tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStopped.name: tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStopped
tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStopped.description: The tmnxDS3E3LoopbackStopped notification is generated when a loopback is removed on a DS3/E3 port. The value of tmnxDS3ChannelLoopback specifies the type of loopback that was configured and has now been removed.

tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStarted.name: tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStarted
tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStarted.description: The tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStarted notification is generated when a loopback is provisioned on a Sonet-SDH port.

tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStopped.name: tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStopped
tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStopped.description: The tmnxSonetSDHLoopbackStopped notification is generated when a loopback test is removed on a Sonet-SDH port. The value of tmnxDS1Loopback specifies the type of loopback that was configured and has now been removed.

tmnxEqPortEtherLoopDetected.name: tmnxEqPortEtherLoopDetected
tmnxEqPortEtherLoopDetected.description: The tmnxEqPortEtherLoopDetected notification is genereated when down-when-looped detects an Ethernet port is receiving PDUs that it transmitted and tmnxPortEtherDownWhenLoopedEnabled is set to 'true'.

tmnxEqPortEtherLoopCleared.name: tmnxEqPortEtherLoopCleared
tmnxEqPortEtherLoopCleared.description: The tmnxEqPortEtherLoopCleared notification is generated when down-when-looped detects an Ethernet port has stopped receiving PDUs that it transmitted and tmnxPortEtherDownWhenLoopedEnabled is set to 'true'. Setting tmnxPortEtherDownWhenLoopedEnabled to 'false' will also cause this notification to be generated if tmnxEqPortEtherLoopDetected had previously been raised.

tmnxEqPortSpeedCfgNotCompatible.name: tmnxEqPortSpeedCfgNotCompatible
tmnxEqPortSpeedCfgNotCompatible.description: Generated when a supported MDA is inserted into a slot of an IOM, the MDA is compatible with the currently provisioned MDA, but the currently configured speed on an MDA port is not compatible with the inserted MDA.

tmnxEqPortDuplexCfgNotCompatible.name: tmnxEqPortDuplexCfgNotCompatible
tmnxEqPortDuplexCfgNotCompatible.description: Generated when a supported MDA is inserted into a slot of an IOM, the MDA is compatible with the currently provisioned MDA, but the currently configured duplex on an MDA port is not compatible with the inserted MDA.

tmnxEqPortIngressRateCfgNotCompatible.name: tmnxEqPortIngressRateCfgNotCompatible
tmnxEqPortIngressRateCfgNotCompatible.description: Generated when a supported MDA is inserted into a slot of an IOM, the MDA is compatible with the currently provisioned MDA, but the currently configured ingress rate on an MDA port is not compatible with the inserted MDA.

tmnxEqDigitalDiagMonitorFailure.name: tmnxEqDigitalDiagMonitorFailure
tmnxEqDigitalDiagMonitorFailure.description: Generated when an SFP/XFP that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring (DDM) enters a failed state.

tmnxEqPortSFPStatusFailure.name: tmnxEqPortSFPStatusFailure
tmnxEqPortSFPStatusFailure.description: Generated when the tmnxPortSFPStatus of an SFP/XFP results in a value other than 'not-equipped (0)', or 'operational (1)'. tmnxEqPortSFPStatusFailure obsoleted tmnxEqPortSFPCorrupted for revision 6.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxQosServiceDegraded.name: tmnxQosServiceDegraded
tmnxQosServiceDegraded.description: Generated when the port is unable to provided the specified quality of service level.

tmnxPortComp7750V4v0.name: tmnxPortComp7750V4v0
tmnxPortComp7750V4v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 4.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7750 SR series systems. tmnxMlImaBundleGroup was added as of R4.

tmnxPortComp7750V5v0.name: tmnxPortComp7750V5v0
tmnxPortComp7750V5v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 5.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7750 SR series systems.

tmnxPortComp7750V6v0.name: tmnxPortComp7750V6v0
tmnxPortComp7750V6v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 6.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7750 SR series systems.

tmnxPortComp7450V4v0.name: tmnxPortComp7450V4v0
tmnxPortComp7450V4v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 4.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7450 SR series systems.

tmnxPortComp7450V5v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 5.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7450 SR series systems.

tmnxPortComp7450V6v0.name: tmnxPortComp7450V6v0
tmnxPortComp7450V6v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 5.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB on the Alcatel 7450 SR series systems.

tmnxPortComp7710V3v0.description: The compliance statement for revision 3.0 of ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB.

tmnxQosAppObjsGroup.description: The group of objects supporting management of Qos associations of the buffer pools to mdas, ports, channels and bundles on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortTestGroup.name: tmnxPortTestGroup
tmnxPortTestGroup.description: The group of objects supporting management of port testing on Alcatel 7x50 SR series system.

tmnxPortObsoleteGroup.name: tmnxPortObsoleteGroup
tmnxPortObsoleteGroup.description: The group of objects in ALCATEL-IND1-TIMETRA-PORT-MIB which are obsoleted.

tmnxPortIngrMdaQosStatR2r1Group.name: tmnxPortIngrMdaQosStatR2r1Group
tmnxPortIngrMdaQosStatR2r1Group.description: The group of objects that describe the MDA QoS discard statistics for an ethernet port located on an oversubscribed MDA for revision 2.1 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortStatsR2r1Group.name: tmnxPortStatsR2r1Group
tmnxPortStatsR2r1Group.description: The group of objects supporting port statistics for revision 2.1 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortNotificationGroupR2r1.name: tmnxPortNotificationGroupR2r1
tmnxPortNotificationGroupR2r1.description: The group of notifications supporting the management of physical ports for revision 2.1 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortNotifyObjsGroupR2r1.name: tmnxPortNotifyObjsGroupR2r1
tmnxPortNotifyObjsGroupR2r1.description: The group of objects supporting physical port notifications for revision 2.1 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortNotifyObsoleteGroup.name: tmnxPortNotifyObsoleteGroup
tmnxPortNotifyObsoleteGroup.description: The group of notifications supporting the management of physical ports made obsolete for revision 2.1 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems. tmnxEqPortSFPCorrupted was made obsolete for revision 6.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortSonetV3v0Group.name: tmnxPortSonetV3v0Group
tmnxPortSonetV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of SONET type ports for revision 3.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortTDMV3v0Group.name: tmnxPortTDMV3v0Group
tmnxPortTDMV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of TDM type ports for revision 3.0 on the Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortATMV3v0Group.name: tmnxPortATMV3v0Group
tmnxPortATMV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of ATM interfaces for version 3.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxScalarPortV3v0Group.name: tmnxScalarPortV3v0Group
tmnxScalarPortV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management for general port settings for revision 3.0 on Alcatel 7x50 series systems.

tmnxPortV3v0Group.name: tmnxPortV3v0Group
tmnxPortV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of physical port capabilities for revision 3.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxCiscoHDLCGroup.name: tmnxCiscoHDLCGroup
tmnxCiscoHDLCGroup.description: The group of objects supporting Cisco HDLC encapsulation on Alcatel 7750 SR series systems.

tmnxMlBundleV3v0Group.name: tmnxMlBundleV3v0Group
tmnxMlBundleV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management MLBUNDLES for revision 3.0 on the Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxObsoleteGroupV3v0.description: The group of objects obsoleted in the 7x50 SR series 3.0 release

tmnxPortEthernetV3v0Group.name: tmnxPortEthernetV3v0Group
tmnxPortEthernetV3v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of Ethernet ports for revision 3.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortTDMGroupV4v0.description: The group of objects supporting management of TDM type ports for version 4.0 on the Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPortATMGroupV4v0.name: tmnxPortATMGroupV4v0
tmnxPortATMGroupV4v0.description: The group of objects supporting management of ATM interfaces for version 4.0 on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.
